## first class usages

:::defs
$$
\newcommand\Usage{\K{Usage}}
\newcommand\Any{\K{Any}}
$$
:::

- new builtins:
  - $\Usage: \star_0$
  - $0, 1, \dotsc, \Any : \Usage$
  - $\mathord+, \mathord· : \Usage →_1 \Usage →_1 \Usage$
- no eliminator; usages are totally opaque
- can compute with them by representing them as e.g.
  `Maybe Nat` and interpreting them to actual $\Usage$
  values just before use
- the ring equations that arise can be solved automatically

$$
\Rule{fun}{
  \TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{π}{\Usage}} \qquad
  \TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{A}{\star_i}} \qquad
  \TyZ{Γ, x: A}{\ChkZ{B}{\star_i}}
}{
  \TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{Π(π·x: A). B}{\star_i}}
}
$$

## move coproduct eliminator to elimination category

:::defs
$$
\newcommand\CaseE[1]{\K{case}_{#1}\:}
$$
:::

- $\K{case}$ can be moved to `Elim`
- its return type will need to be given but it
  can also become dependent

$$
\Rule{case}{
  \TyZ{Γ, x: A+B}{\ChkZ{C}{\star_i}} \\
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Syn{σ}{e}{A+B}}{Θ'} \\
  \Ty{Γ,& y: A}{Θ',& 1·y}{\Chk{σ}{t₁}{C[x \coloneqq \Inl y]}}{Θ'', ζ·x} \\
  \Ty{Γ,& y: B}{Θ',& 1·y}{\Chk{σ}{t₂}{C[x \coloneqq \Inr y]}}{Θ'', ζ·x} \\
  \IN ζ \Empty
}{
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Syn{σ}{\CaseE{x.C} e \: (y. t₁) \: (y. t₂)}{C[x \coloneqq e]}}{Θ''}
}
$$

## packing up usages

:::defs
$$
\newcommand\Box[1]{\square_{#1}\:}
\newcommand\Pack{\K{pack}\:}
\newcommand\Unpack[1]{\K{unpack}_{#1}\:}
$$
:::

- (in case we end up rejecting records)
- $\Box π A$ packs up $π$ uses of an $A$ into a single value

$$
\begin{gathered}
\Rule{box}{
  (\TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{π}{\Usage}}) \qquad
  \TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{A}{\star_i}}
}{
  \TyZ{Γ}{\ChkZ{\Box π A}{\star_i}}
}
\\[1em]
\Rule{pack}{
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Chk{σπ}{s}{A}}{Θ'}
}{
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Chk{σ}{\Pack s}{\Box π A}}{Θ'}
}
\\[1em]
\Rule{unpack}{
  \TyZ{Γ, x: A}{\ChkZ{B}{\star_i}} \qquad
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Syn{σ}{e}{\Box π A}}{Θ'} \\
  \Ty{Γ,& y: A}{Θ',& π · y}{\Chk{σ}{t}{B[x \coloneqq \Pack y]}}{Θ'', ζ·y} \qquad
  \IN ζ \Empty
}{
  \Ty{Γ}{Θ}{\Syn{σ}{\Unpack{x.B} x = e \In t}{B[x \coloneqq e]}}{Θ''}
}
\end{gathered}
$$

